463. The adverb paenissume recurs v. 660. That the first syllable should be spelt with a diphthong, appears from Priscian who in two passages declares paenissime to be the superlative oi paene: see Bitschl's note on Most. 656. This derivationis also borne out by the meaning ‘very nearly.⁷
